Definition: causing to feel shame or chagrin or vexation
Example: the embarrassing moment when she found her petticoat down around her ankles; it was mortifying to know he had heard every word
Synonyms: mortifying, causing, to, feel, shame, or, chagrin, vexation, the, moment, when, she, found, her, petticoat, down, around, ankles, it, was, know, he, had, heard, every, word
Category: adj.all
